files.patch:
@@ -0,0 +1,1 @@
+@echo off
@@ -51,0 +52,4 @@
+REM Log file for Visual Studio batch files, controlled by environment variable:
+REM   VSCMD_DEBUG=n where n = 1 (basic), 2 (detailed), or 3 (trace)
+set VCVARSALL_LOG=build\vcvarsall.log
+
@@ -58,1 +63,3 @@
-call "%VSVARS32%" > NUL
+@echo on
+@call "%VSVARS32%" > "%VCVARSALL_LOG%" 2>&1
+@echo off
@@ -63,1 +70,3 @@
-call "%VCVARSALL%" %VCARCH% > NUL
+@echo on
+@call "%VCVARSALL%" %VCARCH% >> "%VCVARSALL_LOG%" 2>&1
+@echo off

@@ -62,0 +62,3 @@
+                        // Skips sending telemetry to avoid duplicate use of standard error:
+                        // "The process cannot access the file because it is being used by another process."
+                        "VSCMD_SKIP_SENDTELEMETRY" : "1",
@@ -63,1 +66,1 @@
-                commandLine("cmd", "/q", "/c", "buildSrc\\genVSproperties.bat");
+                commandLine("cmd", "/c", "buildSrc\\genVSproperties.bat");
